ğŸ‘‰ A ReplicaSet ensures that a specified number of identical pods are always running in the cluster.
If a pod dies, the ReplicaSet creates a new one. If there are extra pods, it removes them. âœ…
ğŸ”¹ Key Features of ReplicaSet
Ensures high availability of pods.
Provides self-healing â†’ replaces failed pods automatically.
Supports scaling â†’ you can increase/decrease the replicas count.
Works behind the scenes for Deployments (when you create a Deployment, it creates a ReplicaSet).
ğŸ“Œ Example: ReplicaSet YAML
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: ReplicaSet
metadata:
  name: nginx-rs
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx
Here:
replicas: 3 â†’ ensures 3 pods are always running.
If one pod crashes, ReplicaSet spawns a new one.
