ğŸ”„ ReplicationController vs ReplicaSet
ğŸ“Œ API Version â†’ RC: v1 | RS: apps/v1
ğŸ“Œ Selector â†’ RC: Equality-based | RS: Set-based (advanced)
ğŸ“Œ Usage â†’ RC: Legacy | RS: Recommended
ğŸ“Œ Deployment â†’ RC: âŒ | RS: âœ… (used inside Deployments)

ğŸ‘‰ In short:
ReplicationController = Old way (limited).
ReplicaSet = New way (flexible & modern).
ğŸ”¹ Important Note
You rarely create ReplicaSets directly.
In real-world Kubernetes, you usually create a Deployment, which in turn creates and manages ReplicaSets for rolling updates & rollbacks.
ğŸ‘‰ In short, ReplicaSet = The Pod Maintainer ğŸ‘·â™‚ï¸ that guarantees your desired pod count is always running.

